'''PPPoE''' ('''PPP''' '''o'''ver '''E'''thernet) is a network protocol for encapsulating Point-to-Point Protocol (PPP) frames inside Ethernet frames.

== Installation ==
Install {{Package|net-dialup/rp-pppoe}}:
{{Emerge|rp-pppoe}}

Configure system to run ppp, see [[PPP Client|how to configure ppp client]].

== Configuration ==
Provided eth0 should be used for connection:
{{File|/etc/conf.d/net|Add:|<pre>
rc_need_ppp1="firewall net.eth0" # firewall is optional
config_ppp1="ppp"
plugins_ppp1="pppoe"
link_ppp1="eth0"
username_ppp1=''   # set your username
password_ppp1=''   # set your password
</pre>}}

Provide an init script for the PPP device by symlinking to net.lo:
{{RootCmd|ln -s /etc/init.d/net.lo /etc/init.d/net.ppp1}}

== Management ==
{{RootCmd|/etc/init.d/net.ppp1 start
|/etc/init.d/net.ppp1 stop}}

